- Sheets fixture: the spreadsheet ID recorded in issue 31's prior evidence was no longer reachable from any configured account (Spreadsheet was not found), so a new scratch Office-format fixture was created: generated goog-e2e-scratch-sheets-issue31.xlsx locally (3 rows x 5 cols, one formula cell) and uploaded it with `drive upload`, producing a fresh scratch spreadsheet ID used below.

Live checks -- issue 35 (Document Map):

$ goog docs map DOC_ID
Expected: human table with Entry/Index/Page/Line/Kind/Style/Confidence/Preview columns; content after an explicit page break shows a derived page and ExplicitPageBreak confidence; content with no page evidence shows no page.
Observed: table printed with all columns; entries after the inserted page break showed Page 2 / ExplicitPageBreak; the first two entries (heading + inline image sharing one paragraph) showed no page and Unknown confidence.
Result: PASS.

$ goog docs map DOC_ID --json | jq '{revisionId, entries:[.entries[]|{entry,location,kind,style,preview}], documentLocations}'
Expected: revisionId, entries, and documentLocations present; every entry has location.contentLine, location.confidence, kind, and preview.
Observed: matched expectations; entryCount == locationCount == 8.
Result: PASS.

$ jq '{entryCount, locationCount, kinds, confidences, hasRevision}' (structural projection of the map JSON)
Expected: kinds include heading, paragraph, table, and inline-image; confidences include explicit-page-break and unknown.
Observed: kinds = [heading, inline-image, paragraph, table]; confidences = [explicit-page-break, unknown]. table-of-contents confidence and positioned-image kind were not exercised live (no native TOC element in the fixture) -- both remain covered by the existing local mocked tests, noted here as the one skipped live fixture per issue 35's own allowance.
Result: PASS (with one noted, allowed skip).

$ jq '.entries[]|{entry,page,line,kind}' (content-line semantics)
Expected: a heading and an inline image in the same top-level paragraph share content line 1; line numbers advance by top-level block afterward.
Observed: entries 1 and 2 (heading + inline-image) both showed line 1; subsequent entries incremented 2..6 in document order.
Result: PASS.

$ goog docs get DOC_ID --fields documentId,title,revisionId | jq keys
Expected: raw Docs get still returns exactly the requested fields.
Observed: ["documentId","revisionId","title"].
Result: PASS.

$ printf '{"requests":[]}' | goog docs batch-update DOC_ID --requests -
Expected: raw batch-update forwards the body to Google and surfaces Google's own response/error.
Observed: Google Docs API returned 400 "Must specify at least one request" -- this is real, expected Google API behavior for an empty request list, not a goog defect; it confirms the command reaches the API with the given body.
Result: PASS.

